## 3. Backend Architecture Rules

| Layer | Location | Rule |
|---|---|---|
| Config | `app/core/config.py` | Declare env vars in `Settings`; do not read environment variables directly elsewhere |
| Database | `app/core/database.py` | Session factory, `get_db`, engine setup, and schema bootstrap only |
| Security | `app/core/security.py` | JWT encode/decode and password hashing only |
| Dependencies | `app/core/dependencies.py` | Auth dependencies such as `get_current_user` and `get_current_admin_user` |
| Schemas | `app/core/schemas.py` | Pydantic request/response models |
| Models | `app/models/` | SQLAlchemy ORM definitions only |
| Routes | `app/routes/` | HTTP handlers, validation, ownership checks, and route-level orchestration |
| Services | `app/services/` | AI agent, storage, demo reset, queue helpers, and reusable complex service logic |

Guidelines:

- Use ORM/select statements only; never write raw SQL strings.
- Keep route changes focused and avoid unrelated refactors.
- If central schemas or models change, update the API client/types/docs in the same task.
- Product/category/location ownership must always be scoped to the current authenticated user.

